*libmcs-0.5.0 (24 Aug 2007)

  24 Aug 2007; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> libmcs-0.3.1.ebuild,
  libmcs-0.3.3.ebuild, libmcs-0.4.1.ebuild, +libmcs-0.5.0.ebuild:
  Version bump. Change SRC_URI to point to new dedicated Atheme mirror network
  for all versions.

  27 May 2007; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> libmcs-0.4.1.ebuild:
  Stable on mips.

  15 Apr 2007; Peter Weller <welp@gentoo.org> libmcs-0.4.1.ebuild:
  Stable on amd64

  13 Apr 2007; Raúl Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org> libmcs-0.4.1.ebuild:
  x86 stable

  10 Apr 2007; Gustavo Zacarias <gustavoz@gentoo.org> libmcs-0.4.1.ebuild:
  Stable on sparc

  11 Mar 2007; Bryan Østergaard <kloeri@gentoo.org> libmcs-0.4.1.ebuild:
  Alpha love.

*libmcs-0.4.1 (27 Feb 2007)

  27 Feb 2007; Javier Villavicencio <the_paya@gentoo.org>
  -libmcs-0.4.0.ebuild, +libmcs-0.4.1.ebuild:
  New upstream release, needed to fix my fix :(. Also added ~x86-fbsd keyword,
  fixed kde linking, and removed 0.4.0

*libmcs-0.4.0 (27 Feb 2007)

  27 Feb 2007; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> +libmcs-0.4.0.ebuild:
  New upstream release. FreeBSD portability fixes from Javier Villavicencio
  <the_paya@gentoo.org> and KDE KConfig support from Diego Pettenò.

*libmcs-0.3.3 (19 Feb 2007)

  19 Feb 2007; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> +libmcs-0.3.3.ebuild:
  New upstream release.

  04 Feb 2007; Andrej Kacian <ticho@gentoo.org> libmcs-0.3.1.ebuild:
  Added ~x86, bug #165161.

*libmcs-0.3.1 (04 Feb 2007)

  04 Feb 2007; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> -libmcs-0.3.0.ebuild,
  +libmcs-0.3.1.ebuild:
  Resolve autoconf difficulties with previous version.

*libmcs-0.3.0 (04 Feb 2007)

  04 Feb 2007; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> -libmcs-0.2.1.ebuild,
  +libmcs-0.3.0.ebuild:
  Reliability fixes from upstream, closes bug #165228.

  04 Feb 2007; Steve Dibb <beandog@gentoo.org> libmcs-0.2.1.ebuild:
  add ~amd64, bug 165161

  04 Feb 2007; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> libmcs-0.2.1.ebuild:
